segments.Hydrological Assessment:
The specific aims of this study is to carry out relevant technical investigations comprising of flood protection management plan, topographical surveys, hydrologic and hydraulic analyses and design as well as conduct a design review process for previous evaluations/studies.
Similarly, the study will determine the needs/demands and the potential for multipurpose infrastructure development, conduct the required studies/investigations, review the baseline information about the current conditions of existing structures and facilities in the project area as provided by the Client in the initial phase and consequently prepare the detailed engineering designs as an integral part of the scheme. Finally, the consultants will prepare cost estimates, which will form the basis for project appraisal and implementation.
In summary, the following tasks describe the above-mentioned goals: -
•	Carryout hydrological and hydrogeological studies for the target area(s);
•	Undertake specific topographical survey at the basin boundaries;
•	To produce several viable options for flood mitigation schemes;
•	To propose the implementation methodology and recommended engineering solutions; and
•	To supervise the implementation in accordance with the proposed designs.

